<paragraph blockId="19.[317,1271,1000,1481]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Designation of the female 
<typeStatus box="[645,729,1000,1021]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="KRIECHBAUMER" authorityYear="1900" box="[765,997,1000,1021]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Acanthobracon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lagopus">
<emphasis box="[765,997,1000,1021]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Acanthobracon lagopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
– (First label, handwriting) “Bodega central de Honda”; (second label, handwriting) “Bodega central / und Honda / am Rio Magda- / lena, Columbien / Therese v. Bayern”; (third label, reverse second label) “Bisher war nur des ♂ / n. als Fundort / «Amer. mer.» bekannt”; fourth label is the 
<typeStatus box="[937,1021,1086,1107]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">holotype</typeStatus>
card, fifth and sixth labels are with the valid (“recte”) name 
<taxonomicName authority="Brulle" authorityName="BRULLE" authorityYear="1846" box="[641,880,1115,1136]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Myosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtipes">
<emphasis box="[641,813,1115,1136]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Myosoma hirtipes</emphasis>
Brullé
</taxonomicName>
♀ (the two labels are with two different handwriting). – 
<typeStatus box="[475,564,1144,1165]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Holotype</typeStatus>
is in fairly good condition: (1) pinned by mesosoma; (2) head glued to mesosoma; (3) metasoma, right hind coxa and right hind leg glued separately on hind part of first label; (4) right antenna missing; (5) right fore tibia less visible (glued to head).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[317,1271,1000,1481]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Designation of the female 
<typeStatus box="[635,719,1230,1251]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="SZEPLIGETI" authorityYear="1902" box="[750,895,1230,1251]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Bracon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="errotus">
<emphasis box="[750,895,1230,1251]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Bracon errotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
– (First label, my handwriting) “ 
<collectingCountry name="Venezuela" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
/ 
<collectingRegion box="[384,458,1259,1280]" country="Venezuela" name="Merida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Merida</collectingRegion>
”; (second quadratic label, reverse the first label) “539/128”; (third label) “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="SZEPLIGETI" authorityYear="1902" box="[1157,1260,1259,1280]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Bracon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="errotus">Br. errotus</taxonomicName>
” (Szépligeti’s handwriting) / “det. Szépligeti” (printed); (fourth label) “ 
<taxonomicName authority="(Szepl.)" baseAuthorityName="SZEPLIGETI" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[993,1245,1288,1309]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Myosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="errotus">Myosoma errotus (Szépl.)</taxonomicName>
♀ (my handwriting) “det. Szépligeti” (printed) “1906” (my handwriting); fifth label is the 
<typeStatus box="[1186,1270,1316,1337]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">holotype</typeStatus>
card, sixth label is with the inventory number “1248”; seventh label is with the actual name 
<taxonomicName authority="KRIECHBAUMER" authorityName="KRIECHBAUMER" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Myosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lagopus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Myosoma lagopus</emphasis>
KRIECHBAUMER
</taxonomicName>
(det. J. Papp 2009), specimen compared with the female 
<typeStatus box="[1124,1208,1374,1395]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName class="Entoprocta" family="Pedicellinidae" genus="Myosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Solitaria" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Kamptozoa" rank="species" species="lagopus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">M. lagopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Labels 1 and 4 to 7 attached by me. – 
<typeStatus box="[773,862,1403,1424]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Holotype</typeStatus>
is in good condition: (1) pinned by mesosoma (before prescutellar furrow); (2) left flagellum damaged; (3) right fore wing damaged proximally from pterostigma.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="22" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[317,1270,1518,1827]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Redescription of the female 
<typeStatus box="[647,731,1518,1539]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="KRIECHBAUMER" authorityYear="1900" box="[760,988,1518,1539]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Acanthobracon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lagopus">
<emphasis box="[760,988,1518,1539]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Acanthobracon lagopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
– Body 
<quantity box="[1065,1137,1518,1539]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="8.5">8.5 mm</quantity>
long. Left antenna about as long as body and with 49 antennomeres (right antenna missing). Scape in outer-lateral view 1.5 times as long dorsally as broad apically, dorsally longer than ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[1110,1183,1576,1597]" captionStart="Figs 74–83" captionStartId="20.[317,360,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[318,1268,1059,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-304@20.[317,1270,1058,1658]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figs 74–83. Myosoma lagopus (KRIECHBAUMER), comb. n., female holotype: 74–81, female holotype of M. errotus SZÉPL.: 82–83: 74 = scape, pedicel and first flagellomere in outer-lateral view, 75 = head in dorsal view, 76 = head in lateral view, 77 = hind femur with indication of its hairs, 78 = claw, 79 = distal part of right fore wing, 80 = first discal cell of right fore wing, 81 = tergites 1–3, 82 = head in dorsal view, 83 = hind femur" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732045/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 74</figureCitation>
). Flagellomeres 1–3 1.25 times, 1.08 times 1 times as long as broad, respectively, further flagellomeres transverse (i.e. slightly broader than long), penultimate three flagellomeres cubic. Flagellum distally indistinctly attenuating, hairy. – Head in dorsal view less transverse (
<figureCitation box="[980,1052,1662,1683]" captionStart="Figs 74–83" captionStartId="20.[317,360,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[318,1268,1059,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-304@20.[317,1270,1058,1658]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figs 74–83. Myosoma lagopus (KRIECHBAUMER), comb. n., female holotype: 74–81, female holotype of M. errotus SZÉPL.: 82–83: 74 = scape, pedicel and first flagellomere in outer-lateral view, 75 = head in dorsal view, 76 = head in lateral view, 77 = hind femur with indication of its hairs, 78 = claw, 79 = distal part of right fore wing, 80 = first discal cell of right fore wing, 81 = tergites 1–3, 82 = head in dorsal view, 83 = hind femur" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732045/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 75</figureCitation>
), 1.6 times as broad as long, eye 1.6 times longer than temple, tempel receded. Ocelli middle-sized, elliptic, OOL slightly more than three times longer than POL (
<figureCitation box="[694,764,1720,1741]" captionStart="Figs 74–83" captionStartId="20.[317,360,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[318,1268,1059,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-304@20.[317,1270,1058,1658]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figs 74–83. Myosoma lagopus (KRIECHBAUMER), comb. n., female holotype: 74–81, female holotype of M. errotus SZÉPL.: 82–83: 74 = scape, pedicel and first flagellomere in outer-lateral view, 75 = head in dorsal view, 76 = head in lateral view, 77 = hind femur with indication of its hairs, 78 = claw, 79 = distal part of right fore wing, 80 = first discal cell of right fore wing, 81 = tergites 1–3, 82 = head in dorsal view, 83 = hind femur" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732045/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 75</figureCitation>
). Eye in lateral view 1.5 times as high as wide, temple beyond eye 0.7 times as wide as eye and narowing ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[896,966,1748,1769]" captionStart="Figs 74–83" captionStartId="20.[317,360,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[318,1268,1059,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-304@20.[317,1270,1058,1658]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figs 74–83. Myosoma lagopus (KRIECHBAUMER), comb. n., female holotype: 74–81, female holotype of M. errotus SZÉPL.: 82–83: 74 = scape, pedicel and first flagellomere in outer-lateral view, 75 = head in dorsal view, 76 = head in lateral view, 77 = hind femur with indication of its hairs, 78 = claw, 79 = distal part of right fore wing, 80 = first discal cell of right fore wing, 81 = tergites 1–3, 82 = head in dorsal view, 83 = hind femur" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732045/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 76</figureCitation>
, see arrows). Horizontal diameter of oral opening 2.6 times longer than shortest distance between opening and eye. Head polished, face weakly uneven.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[317,1270,436,1005]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Mesosoma in lateral view 1.5 times as long as high, polished. Notaulix distinct, smooth. – Hind femur 3.3 times as long as broad medially and with fairly long hairs (
<figureCitation box="[1012,1083,465,486]" captionStart="Figs 74–83" captionStartId="20.[317,360,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[318,1268,1059,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-304@20.[317,1270,1058,1658]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figs 74–83. Myosoma lagopus (KRIECHBAUMER), comb. n., female holotype: 74–81, female holotype of M. errotus SZÉPL.: 82–83: 74 = scape, pedicel and first flagellomere in outer-lateral view, 75 = head in dorsal view, 76 = head in lateral view, 77 = hind femur with indication of its hairs, 78 = claw, 79 = distal part of right fore wing, 80 = first discal cell of right fore wing, 81 = tergites 1–3, 82 = head in dorsal view, 83 = hind femur" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732045/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 77</figureCitation>
). Hind basitarsus as long as tarsomeres 2–4 combined. Claw downcurved and with wide and somewhat pointed basal lobe (
<figureCitation box="[324,398,523,544]" captionStart="Figs 74–83" captionStartId="20.[317,360,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[318,1268,1059,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-304@20.[317,1270,1058,1658]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figs 74–83. Myosoma lagopus (KRIECHBAUMER), comb. n., female holotype: 74–81, female holotype of M. errotus SZÉPL.: 82–83: 74 = scape, pedicel and first flagellomere in outer-lateral view, 75 = head in dorsal view, 76 = head in lateral view, 77 = hind femur with indication of its hairs, 78 = claw, 79 = distal part of right fore wing, 80 = first discal cell of right fore wing, 81 = tergites 1–3, 82 = head in dorsal view, 83 = hind femur" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732045/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 78</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[317,1270,436,1005]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fore wing as long as body. Pterostigma (
<figureCitation box="[770,839,552,573]" captionStart="Figs 74–83" captionStartId="20.[317,360,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[318,1268,1059,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-304@20.[317,1270,1058,1658]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figs 74–83. Myosoma lagopus (KRIECHBAUMER), comb. n., female holotype: 74–81, female holotype of M. errotus SZÉPL.: 82–83: 74 = scape, pedicel and first flagellomere in outer-lateral view, 75 = head in dorsal view, 76 = head in lateral view, 77 = hind femur with indication of its hairs, 78 = claw, 79 = distal part of right fore wing, 80 = first discal cell of right fore wing, 81 = tergites 1–3, 82 = head in dorsal view, 83 = hind femur" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732045/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 79</figureCitation>
) 3.3 times as long as wide and issuing 
<emphasis box="[1208,1217,552,573]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">r</emphasis>
from its middle, 
<emphasis box="[422,431,581,602]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">r</emphasis>
as long as width of pterostigma. Second submarginal cell short, 
<emphasis box="[1038,1089,581,602]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">3–SR</emphasis>
1.6 times length of 
<emphasis box="[317,368,609,630]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">2–SR</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis box="[382,421,609,630]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">SR1</emphasis>
almost straight, reaching tip of wing and 1.7 times longer than 
<emphasis box="[1049,1100,609,630]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">3–SR</emphasis>
. First discal cell: 
<emphasis box="[317,400,638,659]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">1–SR–M</emphasis>
weakly bent and almost twice longer than 
<emphasis box="[801,844,638,659]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">1–M</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[855,899,638,659]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">1–M</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[943,995,638,659]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">m–cu</emphasis>
not parallel (
<figureCitation box="[1119,1189,638,659]" captionStart="Figs 74–83" captionStartId="20.[317,360,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[318,1268,1059,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-304@20.[317,1270,1058,1658]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figs 74–83. Myosoma lagopus (KRIECHBAUMER), comb. n., female holotype: 74–81, female holotype of M. errotus SZÉPL.: 82–83: 74 = scape, pedicel and first flagellomere in outer-lateral view, 75 = head in dorsal view, 76 = head in lateral view, 77 = hind femur with indication of its hairs, 78 = claw, 79 = distal part of right fore wing, 80 = first discal cell of right fore wing, 81 = tergites 1–3, 82 = head in dorsal view, 83 = hind femur" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732045/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 80</figureCitation>
). – Hind wing: 
<emphasis box="[379,430,667,688]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">1r–m</emphasis>
curved like that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="BRULLE" authorityYear="1846" box="[625,731,667,688]" class="Entoprocta" family="Pedicellinidae" genus="Myosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Solitaria" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Kamptozoa" rank="species" species="hirtipes">
<emphasis box="[625,731,667,688]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">M. hirtipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<figureCitation box="[779,852,667,688]" captionStart="Figs 66–73" captionStartId="18.[317,360,1748,1769]" captionTargetBox="[317,1269,1240,1718]" captionTargetId="figure-332@18.[317,1269,1240,1719]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs 66–73. Myosoma hirtipes BRULLÉ, female holotype: 66 = scape and pedicel in outer-lateral view, 67 = head in dorsal view, 68 = head in lateral view, 69 = hind femur and tibia with hairs, 70 = claw, 71 =distal part of left fore wing,72 =first discal cell of left fore wing, 73 = vein 1r–m of hind wing" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732043" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732043/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 73</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[317,1270,436,1005]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
First tergite (
<figureCitation box="[506,576,696,717]" captionStart="Figs 74–83" captionStartId="20.[317,360,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[318,1268,1059,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-304@20.[317,1270,1058,1658]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figs 74–83. Myosoma lagopus (KRIECHBAUMER), comb. n., female holotype: 74–81, female holotype of M. errotus SZÉPL.: 82–83: 74 = scape, pedicel and first flagellomere in outer-lateral view, 75 = head in dorsal view, 76 = head in lateral view, 77 = hind femur with indication of its hairs, 78 = claw, 79 = distal part of right fore wing, 80 = first discal cell of right fore wing, 81 = tergites 1–3, 82 = head in dorsal view, 83 = hind femur" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732045/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 81</figureCitation>
) five times as long as broad, scutum moderately broadening posteriorly, together with further tergites polished. Second tergite transverse and laterally narrowing, four times broader behind than long medially; third tergite as long as second tergite (
<figureCitation box="[1014,1084,753,774]" captionStart="Figs 74–83" captionStartId="20.[317,360,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[318,1268,1059,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-304@20.[317,1270,1058,1658]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figs 74–83. Myosoma lagopus (KRIECHBAUMER), comb. n., female holotype: 74–81, female holotype of M. errotus SZÉPL.: 82–83: 74 = scape, pedicel and first flagellomere in outer-lateral view, 75 = head in dorsal view, 76 = head in lateral view, 77 = hind femur with indication of its hairs, 78 = claw, 79 = distal part of right fore wing, 80 = first discal cell of right fore wing, 81 = tergites 1–3, 82 = head in dorsal view, 83 = hind femur" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732045/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 81</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor sheath long, as long as hind tibia + half basitarsus combined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[317,1270,436,1005]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Antenna, had, mesosoma, legs and ovipositor sheath black, metasoma reddish. Mandible dark rusty. Upper margin of pronotum rusty. Hairs of legs black. Wings brown fumous, pterostigma and veins brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[317,1270,436,1005]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Deviating features of 
<specimenCount box="[591,697,897,918]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
(
<typeStatus box="[710,796,897,918]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="SZEPLIGETI" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[827,929,897,918]" class="Entoprocta" family="Pedicellinidae" genus="Myosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Solitaria" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Kamptozoa" rank="species" species="errotus">
<emphasis box="[827,929,897,918]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">M. errotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).–Body 
<quantity box="[1013,1068,897,918]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
long. Head in dorsal view 1.5 times as broad as long (
<figureCitation box="[627,698,926,947]" captionStart="Figs 74–83" captionStartId="20.[317,360,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[318,1268,1059,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-304@20.[317,1270,1058,1658]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figs 74–83. Myosoma lagopus (KRIECHBAUMER), comb. n., female holotype: 74–81, female holotype of M. errotus SZÉPL.: 82–83: 74 = scape, pedicel and first flagellomere in outer-lateral view, 75 = head in dorsal view, 76 = head in lateral view, 77 = hind femur with indication of its hairs, 78 = claw, 79 = distal part of right fore wing, 80 = first discal cell of right fore wing, 81 = tergites 1–3, 82 = head in dorsal view, 83 = hind femur" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732045/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 82</figureCitation>
). Hind femur four times as long as broad medially (
<figureCitation box="[1187,1259,926,947]" captionStart="Figs 74–83" captionStartId="20.[317,360,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[318,1268,1059,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-304@20.[317,1270,1058,1658]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figs 74–83. Myosoma lagopus (KRIECHBAUMER), comb. n., female holotype: 74–81, female holotype of M. errotus SZÉPL.: 82–83: 74 = scape, pedicel and first flagellomere in outer-lateral view, 75 = head in dorsal view, 76 = head in lateral view, 77 = hind femur with indication of its hairs, 78 = claw, 79 = distal part of right fore wing, 80 = first discal cell of right fore wing, 81 = tergites 1–3, 82 = head in dorsal view, 83 = hind femur" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732045/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
). Fore wing: 
<emphasis box="[430,482,955,976]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">3–SR</emphasis>
1.5 times as long as 
<emphasis box="[690,741,955,976]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">2–SR</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[754,793,955,976]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">SR1</emphasis>
1.6 times longer than 
<emphasis box="[1014,1065,955,976]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">3–SR</emphasis>
. Outer orbit (of eye) rusty, pronotum and lateral lobe of mesoscutum with faint rusty suffusion.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732045" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5732045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732045/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" startId="20.[317,360,1689,1710]" targetBox="[318,1268,1059,1655]" targetPageId="20">
<paragraph blockId="20.[317,1270,1689,1826]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[317,432,1689,1710]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Figs 74–83.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(KRIECHBAUMER)" authorityName="Papp" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="KRIECHBAUMER" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[438,800,1690,1711]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Myosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lagopus" status="comb. n.">
<emphasis box="[438,614,1690,1711]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Myosoma lagopus</emphasis>
(KRIECHBAUMER)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[811,896,1690,1711]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species">comb. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, female holotype: 74–81, female holotype of 
<taxonomicName authority="SZEPL." authorityName="SZEPL." box="[387,557,1718,1740]" class="Entoprocta" family="Pedicellinidae" genus="Myosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Solitaria" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Kamptozoa" rank="species" species="errotus">
<emphasis box="[387,486,1719,1740]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">M. errotus</emphasis>
SZÉPL.
</taxonomicName>
: 82–83: 74 = scape, pedicel and first flagellomere in outer-lateral view, 75 = head in dorsal view, 76 = head in lateral view, 77 = hind femur with indication of its hairs, 78 = claw, 79 = distal part of right fore wing, 80 = first discal cell of right fore wing, 81 = tergites 1–3, 82 = head in dorsal view, 83 = hind femur
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="21.[382,742,436,486]" box="[382,625,436,457]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Male and host unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[382,742,465,486]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="21.[382,742,436,486]" box="[382,742,465,486]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Distribution – 
<collectingCountry box="[525,622,465,486]" name="Colombia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[633,737,465,486]" name="Venezuela" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[317,1270,526,657]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Taxonomic position – Since SCHULZ’ s synonymization (l.c.) the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Papp" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="KRIECHBAUMER" baseAuthorityYear="1900" class="Entoprocta" family="Pedicellinidae" genus="Myosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Solitaria" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Kamptozoa" rank="species" species="lagopus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">A. lagopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was suppressed as conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authority="(SHENEFELT 1978)" baseAuthorityName="SHENEFELT" baseAuthorityYear="1978" box="[777,1135,561,587]" class="Entoprocta" family="Pedicellinidae" genus="Myosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Solitaria" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Kamptozoa" rank="species" species="hirtipes">
<emphasis box="[777,905,561,587]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. hirtipes</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="SHENEFELT, R. D." box="[920,1126,561,587]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1425 - 1872" refId="ref16276" refString="SHENEFELT, R. D. (1978) Braconidae 10: Braconinae, Gnathobraconinae, Mesostoinae, Pseudodicrogeniinae, Telengainae, Ypsistocerinae, plus Braconidae in general, major groups, unplaced genera and species. In: VECHT, VAN DER J. &amp; SHENEFELT, R. D. (eds): Hymenoptera Catalogus (nova editio) pars 15: 1425 - 1872." type="journal article" year="1978">SHENEFELT 1978</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[475,589,596,622]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">holotypes</typeStatus>
of the two taxa, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="SHENEFELT" baseAuthorityYear="1978" box="[776,903,596,622]" class="Entoprocta" family="Pedicellinidae" genus="Myosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Solitaria" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Kamptozoa" rank="species" species="hirtipes">
<emphasis box="[776,903,596,622]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. hirtipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Papp" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="KRIECHBAUMER" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[956,1086,596,622]" class="Entoprocta" family="Pedicellinidae" genus="Myosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Solitaria" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Kamptozoa" rank="species" species="lagopus">
<emphasis box="[956,1086,596,622]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. lagopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
albeit very near to each other, shows two valid species. Their distinction is presented as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[317,1270,684,816]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
1 (2) Second submarginal cell long, 
<emphasis box="[767,829,684,710]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">3–SR</emphasis>
twice as long as 
<emphasis box="[1027,1089,684,710]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">2–SR</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1104,1191,684,710]" captionStart="Figs 66–73" captionStartId="18.[317,360,1748,1769]" captionTargetBox="[317,1269,1240,1718]" captionTargetId="figure-332@18.[317,1269,1240,1719]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs 66–73. Myosoma hirtipes BRULLÉ, female holotype: 66 = scape and pedicel in outer-lateral view, 67 = head in dorsal view, 68 = head in lateral view, 69 = hind femur and tibia with hairs, 70 = claw, 71 =distal part of left fore wing,72 =first discal cell of left fore wing, 73 = vein 1r–m of hind wing" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732043" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732043/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 71</figureCitation>
). Hind femur with long hairs (
<figureCitation box="[678,766,719,745]" captionStart="Figs 66–73" captionStartId="18.[317,360,1748,1769]" captionTargetBox="[317,1269,1240,1718]" captionTargetId="figure-332@18.[317,1269,1240,1719]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs 66–73. Myosoma hirtipes BRULLÉ, female holotype: 66 = scape and pedicel in outer-lateral view, 67 = head in dorsal view, 68 = head in lateral view, 69 = hind femur and tibia with hairs, 70 = claw, 71 =distal part of left fore wing,72 =first discal cell of left fore wing, 73 = vein 1r–m of hind wing" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732043" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732043/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 69</figureCitation>
). Temple in dorsal view less rounded (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 66–73" captionStartId="18.[317,360,1748,1769]" captionTargetBox="[317,1269,1240,1718]" captionTargetId="figure-332@18.[317,1269,1240,1719]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs 66–73. Myosoma hirtipes BRULLÉ, female holotype: 66 = scape and pedicel in outer-lateral view, 67 = head in dorsal view, 68 = head in lateral view, 69 = hind femur and tibia with hairs, 70 = claw, 71 =distal part of left fore wing,72 =first discal cell of left fore wing, 73 = vein 1r–m of hind wing" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732043" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732043/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
). Fore wing: proximal half of subhyaline, distal half brown fumous. ♀:? 
<quantity box="[421,489,790,816]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
<taxonomicName authority="BRULLE, 1846" authorityName="BRULLE" authorityYear="1846" box="[962,1270,790,816]" class="Entoprocta" family="Pedicellinidae" genus="Myosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Solitaria" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Kamptozoa" rank="species" species="hirtipes">
<emphasis box="[962,1091,790,816]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. hirtipes</emphasis>
