<paragraph blockId="21.[317,1270,843,974]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
2 (1) Second submarginal cell less long, 
<emphasis box="[828,889,843,869]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">3–SR</emphasis>
1.6 times as long as 
<emphasis box="[1143,1205,843,869]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">2–SR</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1222,1270,843,869]" captionStart="Figs 74–83" captionStartId="20.[317,360,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[318,1268,1059,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-304@20.[317,1270,1058,1658]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figs 74–83. Myosoma lagopus (KRIECHBAUMER), comb. n., female holotype: 74–81, female holotype of M. errotus SZÉPL.: 82–83: 74 = scape, pedicel and first flagellomere in outer-lateral view, 75 = head in dorsal view, 76 = head in lateral view, 77 = hind femur with indication of its hairs, 78 = claw, 79 = distal part of right fore wing, 80 = first discal cell of right fore wing, 81 = tergites 1–3, 82 = head in dorsal view, 83 = hind femur" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732045/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig.</figureCitation>
79). Hind femur with less long hairs (
<figureCitation box="[853,942,878,904]" captionStart="Figs 74–83" captionStartId="20.[317,360,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[318,1268,1059,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-304@20.[317,1270,1058,1658]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figs 74–83. Myosoma lagopus (KRIECHBAUMER), comb. n., female holotype: 74–81, female holotype of M. errotus SZÉPL.: 82–83: 74 = scape, pedicel and first flagellomere in outer-lateral view, 75 = head in dorsal view, 76 = head in lateral view, 77 = hind femur with indication of its hairs, 78 = claw, 79 = distal part of right fore wing, 80 = first discal cell of right fore wing, 81 = tergites 1–3, 82 = head in dorsal view, 83 = hind femur" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732045/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 77</figureCitation>
). Temple in dorsal view receded (
<figureCitation box="[492,628,913,939]" captionStart="Figs 74–83" captionStartId="20.[317,360,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[318,1268,1059,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-304@20.[317,1270,1058,1658]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figs 74–83. Myosoma lagopus (KRIECHBAUMER), comb. n., female holotype: 74–81, female holotype of M. errotus SZÉPL.: 82–83: 74 = scape, pedicel and first flagellomere in outer-lateral view, 75 = head in dorsal view, 76 = head in lateral view, 77 = hind femur with indication of its hairs, 78 = claw, 79 = distal part of right fore wing, 80 = first discal cell of right fore wing, 81 = tergites 1–3, 82 = head in dorsal view, 83 = hind femur" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5732045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5732045/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Figs 75, 82</figureCitation>
). Fore wing evenly brown fumous. ♀: 
<quantity box="[1084,1203,913,939]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.25" metricValueMax="8.5" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="8.25" valueMax="8.5" valueMin="8.0">8–8.5 mm</quantity>
<taxonomicName authority="(KRIECHBAUMER, 1900)" authorityName="Papp" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="KRIECHBAUMER" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[838,1269,948,974]" class="Entoprocta" family="Pedicellinidae" genus="Myosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Solitaria" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Kamptozoa" rank="species" species="lagopus">
<emphasis box="[838,970,948,974]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. lagopus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="KRIECHBAUMER, J." box="[986,1261,948,974]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="97 - 107" refId="ref15797" refString="KRIECHBAUMER, J. (1900) Von Ihrer Konigl. Hoheit der Prinzessin Therese von Bayerns auf einer Reise in Sudamerika gesammelten Insekten (Fortsetzung). I. Hymenopteren. Berliner Entomologische Zeitschrift 45: 97 - 107." type="journal article" year="1900">KRIECHBAUMER, 1900</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[317,1269,1012,1073]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
The species is also near to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="BRULLE" authorityYear="1846" box="[698,871,1012,1038]" class="Entoprocta" family="Pedicellinidae" genus="Myosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Solitaria" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Kamptozoa" rank="species" species="rubriventre">
<emphasis box="[698,871,1012,1038]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. rubriventre</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, for their distinction see key-couplets 8 (9)–9 (8).
</paragraph>
